This paper discusses the challenges of generating code with polymorphism and effects, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also presents a novel source-to-source transformation, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the formal justification of the proposed solution, which involves aspects of machine learning (cs.LG), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and data structures (cs.DS).
